summarization.results: Mother Cabrini, a dedicated missionary nun, founded the Missionary Sisters of the Sacred Heart and established schools and hospitals in various locations, including Italy and the United States. She served immigrant communities, particularly Italian immigrants, and her impactful work led to the opening of 70 institutions. In Denver, she founded the Queen of Heaven Orphanage and a summer camp for girls. The Mother Cabrini Shrine stands as a tribute to her legacy.
